caption: It is advertised online that you can bring your dog, so we even called ahead to make sure that we could bring our dog and that there would be heaters and a tent. We then drove there and paid for parking for them to tell us that the heaters in their small tent on the sidewalk in front of the restaurant weren’t working and we could not come inside. Disappointed because really wanted to try it— but should not advertise that you can bring your dog.
Great selection of beers; for lunch try the Kung fu wings or chicken sandwich; Nice juke box

Great beer selection and good food. My only complaint is that they are clearly not following capacity limits nor are they enforcing masks. We didn't feel safe so we moved to outside seating. I wish they were taking things more seriously. Many many people walking around with no masks on and they were 100% full inside
Loved this place. Great atmosphere, friendly staff. We didn't eat but the food looked good.
Good vibes was happy they were open!
Best food, staff, beer selection, and neighborhood watering hole! Been coming here for years and recommend it to everyone. Will not disappoint!!
If you are looking for a laid back cheers type of vibe this is your place!! Nice draft selection and waiter was very friendly and attentive...
stopped by for the first time in early February and very pleased with the cocktails. Good local spot in the South Loop!
Amazing food with a super friendly and helpful staff.
They definitely take pride in.everything they do. A once in a lifetime experience.
Beautiful decor. Exceptional service. Very creative menu with delicious food. Generous portions. Would definitely go back.
The staff and atmosphere are as good as they get and the head chef and possibly owner is great.
The food is as good as it gets, and the service complements it. I had high expectations and they were exceeded
This place absolutely blew me away. The food, the service, the atmosphere, was unique in a way that I have never experienced back home..
The food was so amazing and the service was great! Well done guys, everything we tasted was so tasty!!!
Everything was awesome. Service was excellent. Highly recommended.
Server was educated and kind.  Service was timed perfectly and prompt.  Food was tremendous.  Very fresh and unique menu.
Awesome, awesome dinner. One of the top meals of my life. Excellent!
The food was amazing!! And we had the best waiter and the best people sitting next to us!!
It was very satisfying. A wonderful experience on the food and the service I will recommend it
Amazing experience full of Vegetarian options. Plates were not only delicious but very elaborate.

Waiters were so rude. Felt a like discrimination. The guy at the bar didn't even look at us, he told us to sit outside, nobody came so I went inside again and they gave one table to another couple that arrived after us. It's so sad to see that poor treat to customers. I wouldn't recommend it at all. Sucks!
Best. Sloop. Bar. Hands down.
Great experience, tasty food. Beer selection is amazing!
Highlight of our trip was missing our flight and then finding this absolute gem 🍻
Delicious food love the chili, Burgers and Pizza ... terrific atmosphere very friendly bartenders and owner always want to make you feel comfortable and want you to come back again
Fantastic service
They have 64 beers on tap and they know exactly how to get you what you're looking for. Very knowledgeable bartender. Really chill atmosphere we really enjoyed it.
Nice place and great food. But foods was pricey.
There was quick, helpful, and friendly service. The bill was fair for the quality of the food.
Fast and courteous service. It has a great interior.
Great spot.
Always good quality, good neighborhood bar without any gimmicks.  If you are looking for a relaxed bar, good TVs, without the social pressure, this is the place.
Fantastic food and service. They have a great beer list and the playlist is the best. Highly recommend. Come for lunch and stay for a great football Saturday
Well I just love the atmosphere, and the beer selection is top notch.  I come for the wings too, big and meaty.  Good bar vibes
Great place, great food and drinks, great peolple!
Great food, strong drinks, and the coolest staff
Such a friendly and fun atmosphere. I could come here weekly!
Great craft beer selection and tasty food.
Inexpensive...good atmosphere.
If you want a sports bar with amazing food and beer, this is it. Our server and the bartender were very attentive and nice also.
Nice cozy place, good food and service.
Good collection of beers. And have a variety of food items to choose from. Kind of sports bar so if you are interested in sports then you can give a try. Amazing place.
I  really like the ambiance here. Delicious food and great staffs.
Great food and drinks! Worth the trip to South Loop

Great service! Comfy "ale house". Unique takes on chili and cornbread are excellent. I got extra to go! Introduced to a new (for me) IPA that was an excellent pick by my waitress. Pleasant out door seating. Excellent proximity to the Jazz Showcase. I WILL be back.
I love this bar.
It's my fav bar in the city
Great service, really friendly bar staff, other patrons were very respectful of mask policies. You love to see it!

I stopped by First Draft last week.  They had grab and take away food, so I ordered a pizza and a growler stout.  The service was friendly and the growler was great.  Really great.  The pizza was OK.  I saw some other food coming out that looked good and I would definatly try other menu items and absolutely come back for another stout.  Really great.  This is a great little neighborhood place to check out.  I look forward to COVID ending so I can come hang out here.  Looks like a great vibe.
Service was great and food was delicious! The cocktails were mediocre. You have to call ahead to make reservations. Overall good experience. (Not many vegan options)

First of all, come here for the fantastic draft beer selection. Secondly, stay for the amazing food. Thirdly, enjoy the first two even more because of the wonderful service.  If you've ever walked or driven past and thought "hmmm, this place doesn't look much" don't be deceived. It's a hidden gem and definitely the best bar in the South Loop.
Great people and food for a drink after work

This place is not your average bar/restaurant! Firstly the food is amazing! They have found a way to make the classics fresh and new, while still giving you that bar food you want! Hand cut fires, amazing bbq, delicious sandwiches and salads! So good! The staff is friendly and the service is top notch! We just moved in next door and this is going to be our new spot! Check them out! The awesome patio is open!

Great customer relations, loved the note and the TP, and wonderful comfort food. For us living solo, the contact for work or networking just doesn’t cut it. The take home I got from FD tonight— and the way I was treated so warmly — makes me confident you’re on the right track. Great experience all around.
Good time
Great atmosphere and the staff is amazing! Will always stop in when I’m in Chicago!

All I did was drink and that's not a bad thing.  For a stout guy they've got the best draft tap list that I've seen since I've been to consume in Lake Zurich and that is a tall order.  Cheers again.  Then bed time.  Kbs.  Bourbon county. Begyle barrel aged imperial pajamas and obscurity cherry maple train.  Nice flight.  Thanks Chevy.   Great looking old school bar and cool vibe.

I come back here every couple of months to find the experience has not changed. Come for the pizza and beer.  Servers: friendly, prompt, professional. Food: mostly unimpressive for the price, except for the pizzas - they're delicious. Drinks: I've never had a mixed drink here that was done right on the first try. Not worth the price. Beer: great selection.  It is very common for the bar regulars to sit in the corner of the bar with staff and be loud/obnoxious even when no sporting events are on which ruins an already mediocre experience.  For the price I'd recommend going somewhere else unless you're looking for sports/beer selection/pizza

Yeah this place deserves 5 star... really cool place ...large options for craft  beer fans ...and good thing they never said that a particular options is not on tap..haha....food really good .. Ambience good for a sports bar ....Only thing is it's location it is just block out of loop and it looks like it's far but no it's easily accessible with cta services too.... overall had good time with friends here
Fantastic staff and amazing food. Tap lineup was huge and had a great rotating selection
Absolutely terrific service, food and beer! Highly recommend.

From someone who grew up in a small town with feeling of community and closeness within, this was a great gem to find in an urban bustling city. It had a nice cozy mom and pop feel to it and plenty of historic value left on the inside of it. We stopped in for an early lunch on our last day in the city. The menu for drinks was extensive and easy to navigate. The food menu has some new elements to the standard "bar food" menu in most establishment's. They even had a kid menu to boot. The bar tender was really friendly and helpful. They have plenty of TV's for viewing pleasure of the sports fans. I would definitely love to come back and see what its nightlife there is like!
Perfect place for chill vibes and an ice cold beer!
64 beers on draft, quality bar, and great service (Danny)
Great place. Food is great and the lunch specials are a bargain. The selections of brews are great. The staff are great too.

Warm and cozy unpretentious bar with classic bar eats and a really unique and extensive tap list. The staff are wonderful and friendly and clearly very attached to their job i this cozy neighborhood spot.  Also a good place to catch a game.
Food was decent. The bacon & parmesan brussel sprouts were amazing! Fantastic craft beer selection. Worth the visit.
Great chicago style food. Quick service. Tender is great.
Food good, and terrific beer list.
Cozy place to watch a game and hang out with friends. We watched a football game and enjoyed happy hour good and drink specials. Friendly staff.
Classic Chicago cozy neighborhood bast with comfort food.
Good
Friendly staff, amazing beer selection, sports sports sports, and bar food you actually want to eat. 6 stars
Nice place for a drink and to meet up with friends.  We had a retirement party for a co-worker and we had awesome service. Thanks
Nice place, friendly people.
Solid low-key bar.   Nice spot for Bears games...Busy but not slammed.

Wednesday burguer and beer was fine. I am not that happy with the beers, since I found them watery. This Guinness, for example, more water than anything. Taste was considerably different than the one I tried in another bar in Chicago yesterday.
Great bar to grab drinks and a bite with your coworkers
Great selection of beer, excellent service and very friendly to  out of town guests.

Spent some time here on a Wednesday night. We arrived just before 6pm so were able to take advantage of their 1/2 price appetizer offer - good between 4pm - 6pm on a limited selection of their apps. Grabbed the "loaded fries" with melted cheese, carmelized onions, and bacon...eating healthy :-). Waitress mentioned there's a fried egg on it as well though that is not listed on the menu. It's hard to go wrong with cheese and bacon, but the fries themselves were great. We also had a classic burger (comes with those great fries) and order of cheese curds, since our hearts weren't beating hard enough from the loaded fries. Both dishes were really good.
Spicy hot chicken sandwich, good chili! Really good beers, not too pricey
Great food. Incredible choice of beers.
Nice local bar with great drinks and tacos.
Great selection and great food

Pretty good beer list, decent bar food, and friendly service. The bar itself is pretty - it somehow feels a little sparse, but I think that's mostly because they actually leave some room to move around between the tables.
Amaizing
If you are a Philly cheese steak eater, try the Chicago beef. It's amazing.
Great find in near South Loop. Nice decor. Plenty of screens for games & news. Delicious food + drink.

Great local restaurant, looks like a hole in the wall at first but an overall great experience. Lots of craft beers on tap, tried a 4 beer sampler and wound up ordering 6 of one of the beers on the sampler. Nachos were ok, not used to fake cheese on nachos. Also had the meat lovers pizza. Not typical Chicago deep dish but the thin crust pizza was very tasty. Overall a great experience and would go there again
Friendly staff,  good food.  Very loud on Friday night
Serious beer selection
Really enjoyed my time there. Generally recommend.
I was in town for a conference. Found this local spot with a very solid burger, huge list of beers on tap, and a great vibe.
Great beer list. Nice menu and an old fashioned long thick bar. Just a really nice spot on Printers Row.
I really like this place, great atmosphere, food and beer.

Monday night's they have 3 tacos for $6.00. Im vegetarian, veggie was not an option but the chef made the best veggie tacos I've had (and I've made several trips to Mexico over the last 18 years). The tomato soup is also a bowl of chunky deliciousness. Bravo chef!!!
As I sat at the bar, water dripped on me from the pipes above. The floor was also wet and slippery from the water dripping. I almost slipped an fell on my way to the bathroom.
Very friendly and good service. The food was delicious and a variety of good. Great location and Restaurant. I recommend First Draft.
The food was absolutely fantastic! Loved the flavors
Great neighborhood sports bar. Nothing special really, but they do everything well, have reasonable prices, and lots of TV's. Can't ask for much more.
Very awesome neighborhood bar with a good selection of beers. However, the service is pretty slow. If you’re not in a rush, this is the place!
Great atmosphere, food and service. Sit at the bar, the ladies will keep your glass topped off and your stomach filled!
Loved our food when we went.  Had decent vegetarian selections and good drinks.  Would go again for a special occasion.
Great neighborhood bar! Incredible beer menu and good food.
Great atmosphere
Really loud and super crowded. Not really my style.
Great Chicago Beef and giant beer list. Good prices. Great staff.
Staff is awesome here and the beer list is substantial! The food is always good but sometimes pricey for what it is.
Busy, but fun! The staff was very welcoming. Get the cheese curds, so good! The cheese comes from Wisconsin.

Top notch local bar.  There's a huge selection of draft beers and everything is served in the correct glass.  Be sure to try the food here.  I recommend the pizza and Brussels sprout appetizer.  The fries are fresh cut and delicious.  This is a popular after-work bar and it's also a popular spot for sporting events.  There are plenty of televisions.

(Translated by Google) Really typical pub in America. But the food is not so delicious. In particular, late evening meals are not recommended. There are a variety of draft beers and quite a few whiskeys. I think the price is reasonable to drink only.  (Original) 미국의 정말 전형적인 펍. 하지만, 음식이 너무 맛이 없다. 특히 늦은 저녁의 음식들은 추천하지 않는다. 다양한 종류의 드래프트 맥주들이 있고 위스키 종류도 꽤 있다. 술만 마시기에는 가격이 적당하다고 생각한다.
Food quality was below average but very good beer selection and excellent service.
Good in summer
Great spot! Have amazing selection of beers and the food is good.
Great place to either Pregame or watch a game. Friendly staff and good food

Best little bar I've ever been to in Chicago. Talking heads radio when the touchtunes isn't playing... I'll never come to Chicago without visiting First Draft. I met one of the owners, Shay, because my favorite Talking Heads song came up on the loud speaker. La Fin Du Monde is my all time favorite beer and it's on tap. I can't recommend this bar more!
Great experience with the Restaurant!!! I love this restaurant. Good tasting food and Very tasty, reasonable prices. I recommend First Draft.
Buffalo chicken sandwich is amazing
A great place to get hearty food and great drinks!

Maybe I came on a bad night. I ordered wings and a burger. The burger was very burnt on the outside to the point that I could not even eat it. It was cooked medium but I couldn’t figure out how they burnt the edges so badly. There was no salt on the burger. The bacon was bland and I couldn’t even figure out how people enjoy the burgers. The wings were basic and rubbery. I’ll have to pass on this one. I heard so many wonderful things about this place and I’m very disappointed.
Great neighborhood bar. Nice draft selection super friendly staff, tons of TVs.

If I could give zero stars, I would. One of the gentlemen servers/ bartenders was extremely rude. Not sure if he hated his job, or is but worse service ever!  I don’t normally leave reviews but that’s how you know the service was bad.

(Translated by Google) Good atmosphere and burger excellent, even if a little complicated to take in hand 😊  (Original) Bonne ambiance et burger excellent, même si un peu compliqué à prendre en main 😊
Great variety of draft beer in a very historic part of the city. Great televisions for sports buffs.
Service was so so
Lunch with a big party. Food and many draft beer choices were wonderful. Buffalo chicken lunch sandwich, frezhly made fries and super brussel sprouts were the faves in the group.
Chevy, Megan, Evan. Beer on beer on beer. Great menu - beer and food. Don’t skip this spot.
Moved to the neighborhood back in April and this has quickly become my new watering hole. Danny and the staff a great. Good beer selection. The buffalo wings are great too.

The first draft burger is like three delicious meals in one, including eggs and bacon. While you could do fries or other sides, the Brussels were amazing! Also a good place to watch every MLB game with theb sound off (which I personally prefer). I hear they put on sound for football but cannot verify.
Spiciest Nashville Hot Chicken that I’ve ever had. Speedy and friendly service. Tasty fries. Wide selection of drinks.
So fun, are there late night, great menu
Great beer selection,  good food and more TVs than I can count in the south loop.
We loved, loved the burgers and fried cheese curds.  My sweet potatoes fries were amazing!    Our waitress, Amanda, was very attentive and sweet!  I will be coming back here in the future.
Great beers....awesome staff....best burger
Good evening atmosphere. I've been coming here each night after lollapalooza and it's never been crowded. The drink specials are reasonable and the staff is pretty friendly.
Always very hospitable. Thanks for the pickle hookup Danny! 🍻 You rock!
Nice atmosphere, sat at the bar but bartender was very short when we asked for advice on the beers so we moved to a table so their waitress would help us.
From out of town. Had a great selection of the areas local beer. Great pub food. Friendly bartender. Price was reasonable. Would be good for sports.
Fun, local spot with a great tap list. As a Portlander visiting Chicago, I was not let down!
Locals, beer selection, food (onion rings, Brussel sprouts, burger, pizza...)
Great draft beer selection.
Great beer selection and a really nice staff. Interesting menu. Mostly loved this place because it feels like a neighborhood bar.
Good beer high prices
Bad service! Food was OK. Wont be back!
Fun place, weird spot though.
Quick in and out bar
Good beer list with not the best service.
Excellent food, insane beer list, great staff!
Kind people, kids welcome
Reasonably priced, not very busy during lunch time, which made it a perfect place for a team lunch
Nice bar and grill cool atmosphere with good food.
Nice place, nice beers, a lot a craft beers, a lot of screens too, fast and friendly service.
Don't order an old fashioned. Total disappointment with a very simple drink.
Loved the selection of beer

Stopped in before a show, at the Park West. My girlfriend and I just grabbed a quick bite. Really enjoyed the snacks. I got the deviled eggs, my girlfriend got the "first draft" loaded fries. Both were very tasty.
(Translated by Google) A good selection of beer, you can watch sports  (Original) Неплохой выбор пива, можно посмотреть спорт
Great selection of  craft beers and good food!!
Cool place. Pizza was lovely
Food was good in big portions. The service was incredible. The bathrooms were clean. Nice menu and overall a great restaurant. Come here for good food and a sports bar
Lots of beers on tap. Food was eh.. Not the warmest environment for newbies, but the regulars seemed to like it.  Might try again someday.
?They have a great selection of beer and pub grub
Good food, sports on the many TVs, friendly staff, great cider.
Great beer selection and good bar food. Lots of tv’s to watch sports on.
What a fun bar! Great beer selection and really good food. If I lived in the South Loop I'd pretty much be a fixture here.  Love the name, too.

Every time we come here it takes forever to get the bartender’s attention and it ruins my experience. I’ve tried to give the place many chances. But a watering hole is all it is and would only be my last resort.
Awesome burgers

Great selection of beers.
They have an incredibleb selection of beers on tap. I have only been twice, and am still overwhelmed by the beer selection when getting a flight. Highly recommended!
Beer selection is great
My favorite sports bar in Chicago
Awesome
Great food and awesome draft selection.  If service from the bartender was better I would give it 5 stars.
Great beer and great food in a fantastic atmosphere
Great place with over 60 beers on tap. Definitely try the Porksicles they're amazing.
Great food!
The food here is very good, the beer selection is outstanding, but what makes this place awesome is the staff. The friendliest bartenders in all of Chicago.
Chicken pot pie was good!
visited fri evening i think. i will be bringing family next time.
Delicious food, nice people, and a great beer selection.
Great beer and TV's, perfect for feeling cozy and watching your team!
Great pub in an awesome location.  Check it out!
Overpriced and significantly overrated. Website provides information, employees falsify. Find another place, it will save you the trouble.
Great beer list and solid food.

Stopped here for some drinks as soon as I got to Chicago. Wonderful selection of craft brews! Started with a pint but then upon the recommendation of Kelly (awesome bartender and conversationalist) I switched to the flight of beer. Had several local IPAs that I really enjoyed! I will definitely stop back again on my next trip.
A cool brewery with decent beer.  There were only 5-6 on tap when I was there...2-3 of which I didnt care for.  The ones I liked made up for it.  Worth a check.
Very relaxing place.
Great draft choices and good food. Had the chicken wings which were on point!
Chicken was ok fried too hard you couldn't enjoy it, French fries was good, & the fish was good.
Best bar near the loop! Great people; locals type bar with tons of beer on tap

Generous, EXCELLENT beer selection, offering Hopslam and BCBS Bramble Rye--both special and rare. Comfy and chilled out environment, not too busy or loud. Good service. Food prices are high though. $18 for loaded fries (half off during happy hour) for example. I would not order the loaded fries again. They were very mushy, not very warm, and were mostly cold grilled onions. The pretzel bites were good. Pizzas looked tasty.
Awesome beer selection.
Beer good, staff sucks... So much that 3 is good!
Nice place locals and travelers.

Beer lovers rejoice! One of my favorite sports bars in the city. Televisions literally everywhere, a ridiculous amount of beer on tap, good food, and a nice atmosphere. Not sure what beer to get? Ask for a flight and find one you like before committing. And good news for transplants - there are so many TVs here that you'll often be able to get one of them turned to your favorite hometown team's game, as long as it's available.
Had a blast here, great bar
Somewhat expensive. Have to walk two blocks down for parking.
Great beer list
Great draft beer selection. Classic bar food. What more do you need to know?
Awesome beer cheese soup along with a tasty Italian beef sandwich. Good fast service.
Great new place for me. Food and beer killed it!!!
Found this place on accident. Great food and drink! TV's everywhere!! Awesome staff!
Good neighborhood bar, we switch between here and Kaseys -both great spots!
Amazing! By chance we had Amanda as our server twice this month and she was great on both occasions.
Great tap selection,  sports on all of the tv's, & awesome lunch deals!
Nice place to grab a drink or food. Lots of cheese choices and big portions. Our waitress was cool and very nice.
Great near South loop establishment. Great for a quick bite or a spot to watch a game. Great beer selection too.
Great restaurant but not the best
Excellent excellent service. Great beer selection. Good food. Did I mention excellent service.
Good place
Excellent beer selection with a lot on tap.  I haven't been thrilled with their food, but its better than average for a bar.
Love the beer selection, great place to watch a game
Great place to watch games, eat some food, and enjoy a large selection of beers on draft. Staff is very friendly as well.
Love First Draft for Bears game and getting together with friends!

Christina makes an excellent spicy bloody mary - a must have!! The buffalo wings are delicious!  The beer list is extensive - 64 taps of all varieties, many of which can’t be found elsewhere in the South Loop. The staff is attentive and kind. The patrons are friendly; everyone is here to have a good time and watch sports. This has been my local spot for 1.5 years and I am 160% satisfied.

Amazing beer and food selection! This was the first bar I came to when I moved to Printer’s Row and I’ve been coming here ever since. The staff is incredible, beer selection is endless, and the food is great. This is a place to meet regulars and have an amazing time!!
Great Food and beer.

I found this place while in Chicago for business. I was looking for a place that I could watch an out of town NHL hockey game (on Center Ice). I walked in 10 minutes before puck drop and they put the Pittsburgh/Washington game on for me and left it on the whole game even though other customers were requesting the Blackhawks. The bartender (Katie, I think) was fast and very friendly. I hope to visit them again soon, even if it's not hockey season.
Nice sport dinner

One of the first bars I had the pleasure of spending time in when I first moved into the city last year. The food is great, the service is pleasant, and the atmosphere is exactly what you’d want on a fun but relaxed night out with your friends.

SO GOOD! So many good beers! Get the porksicles!! Those were the highlight of our meal. Fall apart tender and super tasty. The onion rings were also fabulous (as was the buffalo chicken wrap). We will definitely be back! Our waitress was also awesome. Overall great experience.
Friendly staff and my first experience of cheese curds (tasty). Oh, and a decent beer selection too. Good sport bar.

Stopped in here with a friend after hearing positive comments about the solid beer selection and for their half priced pizza night as advertises on their website. Beer was great and pizza was ok but when the bartender presented the bill it showed full price for the pizza. I explained to her that I read online about the half priced pizza and proceeded to show her on my phone their website stating half priced pizza on Thursday (see attached pictures) she informed me with a snarky remark that their website guy was a little slow and it should have been changed a few months ago. This is a very poor and misleading business practice.
Great service. Awesome food!!!
Stopped here at random on our walk through Chicago and was treated to great food, beer and service.  Will come back for sure next time we are in the area.
Great staff, food, ambiance and with 60+ on tap you cant go wrong going to this location. Be prepared to make this ur go to spot when in the loop area.

Hello to my new local bar!!! Just moved to Printer’s Row/South Loop area, and had a great time!!! EVERY server should learn their job from Amanda. She is what makes a place like this epic. We cannot wait to come back again very soon.
Exactly as described. Excellent food, large on-tap beer selection, courteous staff, and classic American bar feel. Football and rock music, a perfect place for Sunday late lunch.
Nice Ambiance and great drink selection
Great beer selection and probably the best place to watch sports in the area. Their food is great as well. I highly recommend trying the porkcicles.
massive selection of beers. great food. great people. go here
Choice of beers
Very hospitable service and wings were great.
Good food, great service!
Beer selection was great, and food was tasty. Service was okay, but had some attention to detail issues. Would definitely go back, though.
Great place for lunch.  Fast service.  Good pub food.

Great Bar. Massive and intricate beer selection that trulu offers something for everybody. Comfertable serting and plenty of tv's. Only thing im upset about is that I didn't discover this South Loop Gem earlier!

The choice of beer on offer is second to none. You can find all sorts of local treasures and other hard to find beers of all varieties here. It's slightly more expensive than the average craft beer place in Chicago but only a little. The food is down to earth and tasty; we enjoyed the pizza and the pot pie.
Pretty tasty burgers, interesting sides, and a great beer selection.

They have a great selection of beers on tap, especially IPAs, all at pretty reasonable prices (several between $6 and $7 for a 16 ounce pour). Our server was great. She gave us some food recommendations and was very patient with our indecisiveness! The taco pizza was decent, but not at all what you would expect from a taco pizza. Reading the description, of course, should tip you off to this. We had an enjoyable evening eating outside, and I would definitely revisit in the future.

First Draft is one of my favorite places to grab a work lunch. The food is consistently delicious and their tap list is one of the best (if not THE best) in the area. If you can't find a beer here you don't like, you just don't like beer.
Great beer selection, tasty food and great service... highly recommend
Great atmosphere! Tons of beer on tap!
The most TVs ina space this size I've ever seen! The tacos are great and plenty of beer choices.

I would not call it a restaurant as it market. It is a sport bar with food served. Food is OK, but not super great. I give 3 stars because of personnel. They should be a bit more polite and not argue with the customers on their choices. Some of the activities were very rude and unprofessional. All in all OK.
Evan was our server. He was very helpful, knowledgeable and enthusiastic! Great beers on tap, nicely (decorated) finished inside. Great downtown location
Absolutely fabulous bar and grill with lovely staff and a whole host of craft beers and lagers. Highly recommended. Oh, and great WiFi

Not bad place to drink.  A bit loud but the food was enjoyable.  Wish I saw how they poured my Guinness cause if you have been to the Guinness factory in Ireland you know there is a right way to pour and a wrong way.

By far my favorite bar in the loop; I have been coming here for a few years now (because it is only a few blocks from the Lassalle Street Metra). Phenomenal food, amazing craft beer selection, and always great service.
Excellent food offerings, adult beverage selection and attentive staff. Sports variety is achieved via numerous TVs. Especially great during NFL season.

Very tasty food. I had the wings and my girlfriend had a burger and both were fantastic. Not the cheapest meal, but very fair pricing. It wasnt super crowded. There were a ton of TVs to watch all the sports on. Will definitely visit again
Bad food and service

Second time there we are from out of town. First time good experience. Food and bartenders. Second time this past Saturday and had a table. Waitress was rude. Walked away before we were down talking without food order. Wanted chips and salsa as one of our orders and she brought back soda water! After getting food she never came back to check on us. Hamburgers were kinda chewy and fatty.
Amazing beer list.  I could literally sit there and read the menu cover to cover.  Food is solid too.
Nice casual place to watch TV sports

Overall: Great specials and great food are the highlights at this surprising gem in the neighborhood.  The good: The food is surprisingly great for a bar, with fantastic specials to pair with it. We went on half-off pizza night, so naturally we got a large pizza for $13 to split for two. It was big enough for probably 5 people, which meant lots of leftovers (which is a good thing!). And the pizza itself was doughy yet loaded with toppings and cheese, it was glorious. They also have a lot of great beer selections, the staff is friendly, and the overall vibe of the place is dive-y but still clean. And, plenty of TVs for games.  The not-so-good: The music was too loud, it was hard to have conversations with our group. They were also playing boy bands all night which, given the older crowd, was not appropriate. Sometimes boy bands are good, that night....not so much.  Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 8/10 Food: 9/10
